name: sut
description:
Suit, suwit, or sut is a way of drawing lots for two people by pitting their fingers to determine who wins. In children's games, the winner of the sut can play first or be freed from guarding. Instead of a draw, a suit used to determine who gets something, or who can start something first.

The fingers used in sut are the thumb which is likened to an elephant, the index finger which is likened to a human, and the little finger which is likened to an ant.
